# Testing

## Unit Tests (Vitest + Testing Library)

- Colocate tests next to source: `src/foo/bar.ts` → `src/foo/bar.test.ts`
- Import test utilities from `vitest`, not from globals
- Use `@testing-library/react` (`renderHook`, `act`) for hooks; use `jsdom` via `@vitest-environment jsdom` pragma when DOM is needed
- Prefer `describe`/`it` blocks; name `it` cases as plain-English behaviours
- Build a `baseState()` helper when tests share a common starting state
- Run with `npm run test` (`vitest run`)

```ts
// ❌ BAD – vague name, no describe grouping
test('works', () => { ... })

// ✅ GOOD
describe('fisherYatesShuffle', () => {
  it('returns a new array and does not mutate the original', () => { ... })
})
```

## E2E Tests (Playwright)

- Place specs in `e2e/` with the `.spec.ts` suffix
- Prefer accessible locators: `getByRole`, `getByText`, `getByLabel` over CSS selectors
- Group related flows with `test.describe`; use `test.beforeEach` for shared setup
- Assert URL and visible headings/text after navigation
- Run with `npm run test:e2e` (dev server auto-starts via `playwright.config.ts`)

```ts
// ❌ BAD – brittle CSS selector
await page.locator('.btn-primary').click()

// ✅ GOOD – accessible role selector
await page.getByRole('link', { name: 'Study' }).click()
```
